cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "CAI Semantic Equivalence Benchmark"
version: "0.2"
date-released: "2026-03-25"
url: "https://github.com/michelejoseph1/cai-semantic-equivalence-benchmark"
repository-code: "https://github.com/michelejoseph1/cai-semantic-equivalence-benchmark"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  A benchmark for measuring semantic invariance in language models.
  Tests whether a model gives the same answer when a question is rephrased.
  380 prompt pairs across 17 domains including factual, math/logic, ethics,
  AI safety, and policy (ecommerce, HR, healthcare, legal).
  Scored with CAI Strain v2, a model-based judge on a 0–1 inconsistency scale.
keywords:
  - LLM evaluation
  - semantic consistency
  - CAI
  - benchmark
  - NLP
  - AI safety
  - policy QA
